title.rendered: Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 3rd T20I: Fantast Team, Probable Playing XIs, Pitch Report

content.rendered:
Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 3rd T20I Fantasy Team

We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable Afghanistan & Pakistan Playing XIs

Afghanistan: Rahmanullah Gurbaz (wk), Usman Ghani, Ibrahim Zadran, Najibullah Zadran, Mohammad Nabi, Karim Janat, Azmatullah Omarzai, Rashid Khan (c), Mujeeb Ur Rahman, Fazalhaq Farooqi, Naveen-ul-Haq

Pakistan: Saim Ayub, Mohammad Haris, Abdullah Shafique/Shan Masood, Tayyab Tahir, Imad Wasim, Azam Khan (wk), Shadab Khan (c), Mohammad Nawaz, Naseem Shah, Zaman Khan, Ihsanullah

Also Read:

Gujarat vs Chennai, Indian T20 League: Fantasy Tips

South Africa vs West Indies, 3rd T20I: Fantasy Tips

Sharjah Cricket Ground, Sharjah Pitch Report

Venue: Sharjah Cricket Ground, Sharjah

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 117

2nd innings average score: 128

Wickets per innings: 6

Type: Slow

Wins

Batting 1st: —

Batting 2nd: 100%

Fantasy Tips of The Day

It has been a dream year with the bat for Imad Wasim: 544 runs at 77 including the highest score of 92*. Aside from his batting brilliance, he has taken 22 wickets.

Only once in his last 10 competitive T20s has Rashid Khan gone wicketless, overall taking 18 wickets. Moreover, he has been a part of the Best11 for the last five T20Is.

Rahmanullah Gurbaz (95 runs and two catches) has featured in the Best11 for four consecutive T20Is. At the Sharjah Cricket Ground, he has collected 218 runs at 36.

Najibullah Zadran has added 110 runs at 37 against Pakistan. His ability to hit clear the smaller square boundaries in Sharjah can generate bonus fantasy points.

In his last 10 professional T20s, Fazalhaq Farooqi has taken a three-for on three occasions. In Sharjah, he has picked seven wickets.

Tayyab Tahir has been experiencing a decent run with the bat lately. He has accumulated 354 runs, including four fifties in his last 10 white-ball games.

Ihsanullah has regularly found ways to impress with the ball, taking (13) wickets in his last 10 professional T20s, including three in the ongoing series.

Shan Masood has been a part of the Best11 in three of his last five T20Is. Besides Mohammad Rizwan and Babar Azam, he has been the only Pakistani batter to average over 30 since 2022.

Abdullah Shafique has now been dismissed for four ducks in succession in T20Is.
